{{/*
  mongod.conf for standalone MongoDB (Go text/template strict, ADR-010). Context:
  .vars.config - the FULL merged mongod object (net/storage/security/systemLog +
  computed/passthrough values), assembled in scenario compute.mongo_config. Rendered AS A
  WHOLE via toYaml (a Soul Stack custom function, docs/templating.md §3.3 "Custom
  functions").

  ★ MongoDB vs redis: mongod.conf is nested YAML (subtrees), not flat key-value.
  So the whole object is serialized via toYaml as one block, not ranged key by key.
  Host-layout (dbPath/port/authorization/systemLog.path) is already MERGED into
  .vars.config (scenario), bindIp=0.0.0.0 is host-invariant (Ansible mongodb role
  default) - so there is no per-host logic in the template (unlike redis.conf.tmpl's
  bind .self.network.primary_ip).

  CRITICAL directives set by compute.mongo_config (see covenant.yml):
    - net.bindIp/port - the listener (0.0.0.0 + net_port);
    - storage.dbPath/engine - the WiredTiger data working directory (data_dir);
    - storage.wiredTiger...cacheSizeGB - cache size (from memory_mb/wiredtiger_cache_gb);
    - security.authorization: enabled - authentication ENABLED (access under
      default_admin; first admin via localhost-exception, community.mongo.user plugin);
    - systemLog.destination/path/logAppend - log into log_dir/mongod.log.
  We do NOT set processManagement.fork: mongod runs under systemd (Type=forking with
  --config without fork - the systemd unit carries fork/pidfile if needed; for PILOT,
  foreground under systemd).
*/}}
{{ toYaml .vars.config }}
